HEADWORD: Callithump
<hw>Cal"li*thump`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A somewhat
riotous parade, accompanied with the blowing of tin horns, and other
discordant noises; also, a burlesque serenade; a charivari.</def>
<mark>[U. S.]</mark> <altsp>[Also spelled
<asp>callathump</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Callithumpian</ent>⟦br⟧
